TranscriptionJob keeps the generated controller
and service-manager shell, but the handwritten
runtime client overrides lifecycle handling for
FAILED, CANCELING, and CANCELED while still
using generatedruntime request projection plus
read-after-write follow-up.
ACCEPTED and IN_PROGRESS remain the provisioning
states for both create and update. SUCCEEDED is
the only steady success state, FAILED is
terminal, and CANCELING is a terminating
breadcrumb during normal observe.
Delete confirmation is explicit repo-authored
behavior: CANCELING and CANCELED are
intermediate delete breadcrumbs only, and the
finalizer is retained until GetTranscriptionJob
confirms the resource is absent rather than
stopping at CANCELED.
Only displayName, description, freeformTags, and
definedTags reconcile in place. compartmentId is
replacement-only, there are no secret side
effects, and the auxiliary
CancelTranscriptionJob API remains outside the
published controller surface.
The pinned terraform-provider-oci revision has
no matching speech resource, so the import
catalog for this row is SDK-shaped and
repo-curated; the runtime semantics in this file
are the authoritative formal input for diagrams
and generator binding.
